**Section 1 – User Story**

**1. User Story

1.1 Epic Story**

As a vehicle owner/hirer who wants URA to follow up with the hirer or driver responsible for URA parking offences, I want to use the Online Customer Portal to furnish the particulars of the hirer or driver (refer to Appendix E of Annex 1A), so that the parking offences will be redirected to the actual hirer or driver responsible.

**1.2 User Stories**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**1.3 Key Functions and Features**

| Functions | Description |
| --- | --- |
| View Outstanding Furnishable Notices in eService | It enables the owners or hirers to access a comprehensive view of their outstanding furnishable notices, providing them with the ability to track notices that require furnishing. It also displays pending submissions awaiting approval, along with the approved submissions for the past X months. |
| Furnish Submission via eService | It allows the vehicle owner or hirer to submit the driver’s or hirer’s particulars for selected notice(s) through the eService portal. The process includes selecting the notice(s), filling in the Furnish Particulars form, eligibility checks, validation of data and supporting documents, review and declaration, and submission to the OCMS Internet backend for processing. |
| Handling of Furnish Submission Outcomes (Success &amp; Failure) | If furnish submission is successful, the eService will display the confirmation message along with transaction details, notice information, and furnished particulars, and provides options to furnish another notice or print the submission. If the submission fails, the eService will display the failure message and reason for the failed transaction. |
| Furnish Process in OCMS Backend | OCMS backend processing after a furnish submission is received, including validation, saving to Internet and Intranet databases, syncing records via CRON jobs, auto/manual approval workflows, sending replies to vehicle owner/hirer/driver on their submissions using the staff portal, updating offender indicators, and changing the notice’s processing stage and amount payable based on the furnishing outcome. |

**Section 2 –View Outstanding Furnishable Notices in eService** 

**
2.1 Use case
**

- The "Furnish Driver’s or Hirer’s Particulars" eService allows vehicle owners or hirers to view outstanding notices that they need to furnish. 
- Owners or Hirers must log in to the system to access their notices. There are two login options depending on the user type:
- **Individual Users: **Login via NRIC or FIN using SingPass.
- Business Users (Company): Authorised Corppass users granted access by their companies will login via SingPass.

- After selecting a login option, the User will be redirected to the Singpass portal to complete the login process.
- If authentication is successful, the OCMS backend retrieves the notice(s) from the database and checks each notice to determine:Whether the notice is furnishable
- Whether the submitted furnishing request is still pending approval.
- Whether a previously submitted furnishing request has been approved.

- The notice(s) will be returned to the eService Portal, and the result will be classified and displayed onscreen:Furnishable Notices: Notices that can be selected for furnishing.
- Non-Furnishable Notices: Display the message for Notices that cannot be furnished if there are non-furnishable notices under the owner/hirer’s ID.
- Pending Submissions: Notices that have been furnished but are pending approval.
- Approved Submissions: Notices for which furnishing has already been completed and approved.

**2.2.2 Login with Singpass to View Outstanding Furnishable Notices
**

- As part of furnishing driver’s particulars, the user must first select either ‘Individual User’ or ‘Business User’ to login with Singpass to initiate the search function.

- After selecting the login user type, the User will be redirected to the Singpass portal to authenticate using their Singpass credentials. Business users with multiple Corppass accounts under different entities will be redirected to the Corppass portal to select the desired UEN. 
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- If the login is successful, the eService Portal will proceed to retrieve the furnishable notices.

- If the login is unsuccessful, the eService Portal will redirect the user back to the Furnish Driver’s or Hirer’s Particular page as shown in Section 2.3.1. 
**2.3 Check notice has existing furnished record and sort notice(s) by submission status**

**
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

![](data:image/x-emf;base64,) ![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

- From the matching results, the OCMS checks whether the notices have already been submitted for furnishing, determining whether they are **furnishable** or **non-furnishable**.

- For the notices classified as furnishable notices, they proceed to the next checking process to ensure the notice is eligible for furnishing. 

- For notices that have been submitted for furnishing, the system checks their submission status. This determines whether the status is Pending, Resubmission, Approved or Rejected.
If the submission status is **Rejected** or if the record indicates it has not yet been furnished to the driver, the notice will be added to the furnishable notice list.

- If the submission status is Pending, Resubmission or Approved for furnishing to the driver, the notice will not be included in the furnishable notice list.

- After the completion of the submitted furnish eligibility check, the furnishable list is ready to check for 

- The possible values are: 

| List Type | Classification | Explanation |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Furnishable List | Furnishable | The notice is eligible for furnishing, and users can proceed with the necessary actions to complete the furnishing process. |
| Pending List | Non-furnishable | The Notice has been submitted for furnishing and is waiting for approval. Notices with submission status = ‘Pending’ (first submission) or ‘Resubmission’ (second submission onwards). |
| Approved List | Non-furnishable | The Notice has already been approved for furnishing. Notices with submission status = ‘Approved’. |

**2.4 Check Notices are Furnishable 
**The list of Furnishable Notices is then put through a check to determine whether each notice meets the required eligibility criteria for furnishing.**
**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

| No. | Process Name | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Start | The process begins. |
| 2 | Process Next Record in FurnishableNotice List | The system begins processing the next Notice in the list of furnishable notices. |
| 3 | Check Offence Type | The system checks the offence type associated with the notice. If the offence type is not Parking Offence ‘O’ or Type ‘E’, the notice is not eligible to furnish and removed from the furnishable list and it proceed to Step 7 to check the next record. If the offence type is ‘O’ or ‘E’, the system proceeds to next step to check. |
| 4 | Check Notice is ANs Notice | The system checks if the an_flag of the notice is ‘Y’. and AN flag notice is not allowed for furnish particular. That AN notice will be removed from the furnishable list. If the notice is not Ans notice, it proceed to Step 5. |
| 5 | Retrieve notice details from the database | The system queries the eocms_suspended_notices table using the Notice Number. |
| 7 | Check notice is suspended with PS | When the list of suspended records of the notice(s) is received, the system checks on each record whether the Notices are PS-ed. If the notice is under PS suspension or has an active PS record, that notice is not eligible for furnishing and is removed from furnishable list. If the notice is not suspended with PS, it’s furnishable and the notice remain in furnishable list. |
| | | |
| 8 | Check Notice’s processing stage are eligible to furnish? | The system verifies whether the notice’s last processing stage (i.e., the current processing stage) is included in the stages eligible for furnishing. If the last processing stage is among the eligible stages, the notice remains in the Furnishable List . Eligible stages for the last processing stage: ROV, ENA, RD1, RD2. If the last processing stage is not among the eligible stages, the system evaluates the next processing stage. If the next processing stage is among the eligible stages, the notice remains in the Furnishable List. Eligible stages for the next processing stage: RD1, RD2. If the next processing stage is not among the eligible stages, the notice is deemed not eligible for furnishing and is removed from the Furnishable List. |
| 9 | Last Record? | After the process has been completed, OCMS checks whether all records in the furnishable list have been processed. If there are more records, the process repeats for the next record. If all records have been processed, the process ends. |
| 8 | End | The process to check notices are eligible for furnishing ends. |

- If there are outstanding Notices that cannot be furnished, the eService displays a message informing users that there are outstanding notices which cannot be furnished and will provide the link to the payment e-service.
- Notices identified as pending and approved will display details of the submissions.

**Section 3 – Furnish Submission via eService**

**
3.1 Use case**

- This Furnish Driver’s or Hirer’s eService allows the vehicle owner or hirer to furnish the driver's or hirer's details for parking offence notices.

- The vehicle owner or hirer selects the specific notices for which they wish to submit the driver's or hirer's particulars.

- Each submission can only be used to furnish details for one driver or hirer for multiple notices and vehicles. To furnish information for another driver or hirer, a new submission must be created.

- The eService provides a Furnish Particulars Form for filling up and submitting the Driver’s or Hirer’s particulars.

- After entering the details, the vehicle owner or hirer is prompted to review the particulars. They must then declare that the information submitted is accurate and true before finalizing the submission.

**3.3 Review Furnished Particulars Before Submission**

The review step serves as a summary of the information provided by the user in the **Furnish Particulars Form**. All data fields displayed at this stage reflect the entries previously submitted by the user. For a detailed list of the data fields, please refer to **Section 3.2.2.**.

The primary purpose of this step is to allow users to verify the accuracy of their submissions and to formally declare the accuracy of the furnished information before final submission.

As part of this process, a **Declaration section** is included to ensure the user formally acknowledges the truthfulness of the submitted information and the legal implications of false declarations.

- My Declaration of Truthful and Accurate Submission

**Section 4 - Handling of Furnish Submission Outcomes (Success &amp; Failure)**

**
4.1 Use case
**

- After the furnishing has been submitted, OCMS Internet backend (BE) responds to the eService Portal, indicating whether the submission was successfully received or has failed due to validation or system errors.

- When the eService Portal receives the furnish submission status, it will display a success or failure message on the UI to notify the vehicle owner or hirer of the submission result. An acknowledgement email will also be automatically sent to the vehicle owner or hirer to acknowledge the submission received . 
**
**

**
4.2 Process Flow**

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

| 3 | Check for Mandatory Data | The internet backend checks whether all mandatory fields are present. (a) If any mandatory data is missing. OCMS responds to eService “Missing data” and ends the process. (b) If the mandatory data is present, OCMS proceeds to Step 4. |

(b) If the save was successful, OCMS responds to eService with “Furnish Submission Successful” and ends the process. |

**Section 5: Furnish Process in OCMS Backend**

**5.1 Use case
**

- The eService sends the submitted driver’s or hirer’s particulars to OCMS via the Internet API.
- The Internet Backend performs the necessary data requirement validation and stores the furnished record in the database.

- If the Furnished Particulars Data is successfully stored in the database, the eService will respond that the submission has been successfully received. If there are errors in data validation or during the data storage process, the eService will respond that the submission has failed.

- The OCMS Intranet supports the Furnish Hirer/Driver eService Portal through the following key functions:Notice Synchronisation: Sync offence notice details from the OCMS Intranet to the Online Portal, enabling vehicle owners or hirers to furnish the driver or hirer particulars for their offences.

- Furnished Submission Processing: Manage the processing workflow to determine whether furnished particulars can be auto-approved, require manual review, or must be resubmitted.

- Once a decision is made, OCMS updates the Online Portal so that vehicle owners or hirers can view the outcomes of their submissions.

5.2.1 Furnished Submissions Data Save in the Internet Database 
**

- All Furnished Particulars submitted via the Furnish Hirer/Driver eService Portal are stored in the eocms_furnish_application table in the PII Internet database. 

- The PII database is used to store all personal information used by the eService. 

- All personal data in the PII database are stored in encrypted form. Examples of fields which are encrypted include ID numbers, name and contact information.  

- The fields in the eocms_furnish_application table in the OCMS Internet Backend are based on:
Existing fields in CAS’ ECAS_FURNISH_APPLICATION internet database
- Fields in OCMS’ ocms_offence_notice_owner_driver intranet database

**
5.3 Intranet Backend Processing for Furnished Hirer and Driver from the eService
**

- The OCMS Intranet Backend runs a scheduled job to synchronize Furnish Submissions from the Internet to the Intranet for processing, to determine whether the furnished particulars can be auto-approved or require manual review.

- Please refer to Section 2 of the OCMS 41 Functional Document (v1.1) for details on the processing of Furnished Hirer and Driver submissions in the OCMS Intranet.

**5.4 Saving and Updating Furnished Particulars After Furnish Submission Approval**

- OCMS uses APIs to send Notice updates in real time to the Internet backend for storage in the Internet DB.

- This keeps the Intranet and Internet databases aligned for Intranet changes and reduces data mismatches.

- It also ensures motorists see the latest Notice updates on the eService Portal when furnishing the Hirer/Driver.
**5.4.1 Update Furnish Submission Status when a Furnished Submission is approved

**1. The OCMS Intranet backend update the status in the ocms_furnish _application database when a Furnished Submission is approved.**
